I want to give this Domino's 5 stars for the pizza, but one star for the website.  In order to get the $7.99 large, you have to order online.  Worst website ever for user friendliness. And I say that with 20 years experience of online buying.  But the pizza....  Because of the deal, I decided to give Domino's another try.  It has been about 4 years since Domino's opened close enough to make it an option.  Except for the website, I am glad I did.  This is the best tasting, best looking pizza I have gotten from Domino's  in Buffalo.  I think the secret, for me, is getting the hand tossed crust.  In past years I'd tried the regular and the thin crust.  In those pizzas each slice had 2 green beans, 1 or 2 pieces of sausage, and 1 or 2 mushrooms.  Always gave the impression  toppings were put on by computer.   This one looks like a pizza I'd make myself.  Another secret for me is getting carryout.   No problem with late and/or cold pizza.
